longBusinessSummary: Toyota Boshoku Corporation manufactures and sells automotive interior systems and products, automotive filter and power train equipment components, automotive components, and fabric goods in Japan. The company offers seats, door trims, and leather instrument panels; headliners, such as ceiling-mounted rear entertainment systems and panorama roofs; headliner and instrument panel mystic illumination, and illuminated twin consoles; and floor carpets, tonneau covers, package trays, electric sunshade systems, and silencers. It also offers textile components comprising seat fabrics, curtain-shield airbags, seatbelt webbings, and partition nets; and exterior components consisting of bumpers, fender liners, and engine undercovers. In addition, the company provides filter products, including air and oil filters; anti-allergen and deodorizing cabin, pollen removal cabin, anti-bacterial and mould resistant cabin, and clean air filters; and hydrocarbon absorption filters. Further, it offers air induction part products, such as air induction systems and cleaners, intake manifolds, and cylinder head covers; fuel cell part products comprising stack manifolds and separators; and motor core components for hybrid systems, fluid filters for automatic transmission, oil mist separators, revolving sensors, ignition coils for motorcycles, and ABS coils. Additionally, the company provides aircraft and railway seats, as well as fabric wall decorations for home interior applications. Toyota Boshoku Corporation was founded in 1918 and is based in Kariya, Japan.
